This paper discusses the limitations of the journal impact factor, which is a metric commonly used in the field of computer science to evaluate the quality of journals. The paper also suggests the need for better certification of journal procedures to improve the quality of published science. Given these topics, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
